Description. Male (
Holotype
).

Carapace and chelicerae orange (
Fig. 54A
). Endites light orange; labium orange. Sternum light orange, with darker margins (
Fig. 54B
). Palps yellow (
Fig. 55A‒B
). Legs brownish yellow, with pairs I‒II darker. Dark pigment filling the femur, patella and tibia of legs I‒IV. Metatarsus and tarsus lighter, compared to the other leg articles (
Fig. 54C‒E
). Abdomen dark grey, with ventral region lighter (
Fig. 54A‒B
). Total length 2.84; carapace 1.38 long, 1.02 wide. Anterior lateral eyes near the anterior margin of the carapace, projecting anteriorly. Chelicerae not projected (
Fig. 54A
). Palps: tibia slightly incrassated, with the dorso-ventral diameter shorter than the bulb; bulb rounded, mid-portion and embolus of equal length; embolus tubular, curved and tapered, with slightly twisted tip (
Fig. 55A‒B
). Legs: robust and coated with setae (
Fig. 54C‒E
); tarsal brush of putative chemosensory setae present in legs II‒IV. Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg mearsurements: I, femur 1.44, patella 0.56, tibia 1.26, metatarsus 1.28, tarsus 0.4, total 4.94; II, 1.44, 0.52, 1.22, 1.24, 0.46, 4.88; III, 1.1, 0.44, 0.78, 0.84, 0.42, 3.58; IV, 1.2, 0.56, 1.0, 0.94, 0.42, 4.12. Macrosetae: I, femur d0-0/1-1-0-1-0-2, p0-0-0-0-0-2/1-1; tibia d0-0-0-0-1/0-0-0, p1/0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp1-0-1-0-1/0-0-1, vr1-0/1-1-0-1-0-1, r1-0-1-0-1-0-1; metatarsus p0-0/1- 0-0-0-0-0, vp1-0-0-1(seed-shaped/apophysis)-0-0-1(cylindrical shaft with abrupt pointed tip), vr0-0-0-1-0-0-1; II, femur d0-0-1/0-1-1-0-2, p0-0-0-0-0-1/0-1; tibia p0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp0-0-0-0-0-0-0/1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0-1, r1-1-0-1-0-1- 0; metatarsus vp1-0-0-1-0-0-1, vr1-0-0-1-0-0-1, r0-1-0-1-0-0-0; IV, femur d0-1/0-0-1-1-1-0, r0-0-0-0-0-1-0; tibia vp0-1-0-0-0-0-0; metatarsus vp0-0-0-0-0-0-1, vr metatarsal comb with 4 macrosetae.

Female (Paratype—CAS 9046549).
Coloration of carapace, chelicerae, endites, labium, and abdomen as in male (
Fig. 54F‒G
). Palps brownish yellow, gradually darkening to distal direction. Legs orange, with pairs I‒II darker, and dark pigment filling the distal region of the femur and patella, and tibia in its entirety; metatarsus and tarsus without dark pigment (
Fig. 54H‒I
). Total length 4.6; carapace 1.7 long, 1.14 wide. Carapace sparsely coated with setae. Chelicerae not projected (
Fig. 54F
). Legs: robust and coated with setae; legs I‒II with ventro-prolateral and ventro-retrolateral tibial and metatarsal macrosetae of different sizes (
Fig. 54H‒I
). Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 1.26, patella 0.62, tibia 1.0, metatarsus 0.9, tarsus 0.36, total 4.14; II, 1.16, 0.52, 1.0, 0.88, 0.36, 3.92; III, 0.88, 0.5, 0.64, 0.62, 0.34, 2.98; IV, 1.2, 0.58, 0.86, 0.72, 0.34, 3.7. Macrosetae: I, femur D0-0- 0-0-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-1-0-0; tibia P0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp1-1-1-1-1-1-0, vr1-1-1-1-1-1-1, R0-1-0-1-0-1-0; metatarsus vp1-1-1-1-1-1-1-1, vr1-1-1-0-1-1-1-1 (
Fig. 54H‒I
); II, femur D0-0-0-0-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-0-1-0; tibia P0-1-0-1-0-1- 0, vp1-0-1-0-1-0-1, vr1-1-1-1-1-1-1; metatarsus vp1-1-1-1-1-1-1, vr1-1-0-1-1-1-1; IV, metatarsus vr metatarsal comb with 3‒4 macrosetae. Internal genitalia: anteriror receptaculum with the dorsal lobe shorter than the ventral lobe, and glandular ducts plate located in the median region of the receptaculum, with the proximal region expanded (
Fig. 55C‒D
).
